snippet.textDisplay:
Fire upon fire watch the meek burn
To each one teach one for the weak to learn
Speak in tongues for the spells we earn
Until hell is just a thought returned
The souls hunger for a greater feat
Than the images we feed it off these ghetto streets
A filthy streak of politicians smiling deceit, signing the sheets
Only real when we believe they have that power over me
Seek your truth to see the power that they seek
Seek within to see the hours obsolete
What's a number to infinity showered over peace
Peace of mind devours a raging war
To elevate this energy to a melody cure
Heavenly pure when the ebony soar
And self hatred is just a thought that was never before.
